Shiny Privacy Policy
Effective Date:
Feb 03, 2025
Welcome to Shiny, a mobile application owned and operated by Shiny Cardboard LLC ("Company," "we," "us," or "our"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information when you use the Shiny mobile application ("App"). By using our App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. If you do not agree, please refrain from using the App.
Eligibility
Shiny is available to users who are 13 years of age or older. If you are under 18, you must have permission from your parent or legal guardian to use this App. We do not knowingly collect personal information from users under the age of 13. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal data, we will take steps to remove such information from our servers.
Information We Collect
We collect the following types of information when you use the Shiny App:
Information You Provide to Us
Account Information
- When you create an account, we collect personal information such as your name, email address, password, and any profile information you choose to provide.
Trading Card Listings
- When you list trading cards for sale, trade, or purchase, we collect details about the item, including images, descriptions, and pricing.
Collection Data
- When you add items to your collection, we may use this data to build a profile of the types of products you are interested in and we may use this information to selectively target you for suggested products.
Communication Data
- If you contact our support team or communicate with other users through the App, we collect messages and related metadata.
Information Collected Automatically
Device Information
- We collect information about your device, including your operating system, device model, and unique device identifiers.
Usage Data
- We gather data related to your interactions with the App, such as search queries, viewed trading cards, and transaction history.
Location Information
- With your consent, we may collect and process your location data to provide relevant trading card listings and trading card market information. We also may use your selected currency to make assumptions about your geographical location.
Information from Third-Party Sources
We may receive information from third-party services, such as Google Play and Apple App Store, when you sign in using your account credentials from these services.
How We Use Your Information
We use your information to:
Provide, maintain, and improve the functionality of the App.
Enable trading card listing, buying, selling, and trading features.
Personalize the user experience and recommend trading cards based on your preferences.
Prevent fraud, enforce our terms of service, and comply with legal obligations.
Respond to user inquiries and provide customer support.
Conduct analytics and research to enhance the App’s performance.
Suggest products and services you may be interested in engaging with.
How We Share Your Information
We may share your information in the following ways:
With Other Users
- Publicly available trading card listings, including your username and listing details, may be viewable by other users.
With Third-Party Service Providers
- We may share data with vendors who assist in app functionality, such as payment processors, hosting services, and analytics providers.
With Legal Authorities
- If required by law or to protect our rights, we may share user data with regulatory bodies or law enforcement agencies.
With Business Partners
- In the event of a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, user data may be transferred as part of the transaction.
Data Retention
We retain your information as long as your account is active or as needed to fulfill legal obligations. Upon account deletion, we will remove or anonymize your personal data unless required for compliance with legal or regulatory requirements.
Security Measures
We implement security measures to protect your personal data from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
Your Choices and Rights
You have the following rights regarding your data:
Access & Correction
- You can review and update your account information at any time.
Account Deletion
- You may delete your account through the App settings or by contacting support.
Marketing Preferences
- You may opt-out of marketing communications via the settings in the App.
Location & Tracking
- You can disable location tracking in your device settings.
Third-Party Links & Services
The App may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for their privacy practices, and we encourage you to review their privacy policies before interacting with them.
Children’s Privacy
Shiny is not intended for children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect information from minors under this age. Parents or guardians who believe their child has provided us with personal data should contact us immediately.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be posted within the App, and we encourage users to review it regularly. Continued use of the App constitutes acceptance of any updates.
